      <pb n="1"/>
        <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Savannah</placeName> <date>May 2d. 1854</date></p>
        <p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philad</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Dear sir</p>
        <p>Your last favour with Invoice<lb/> came duly to hand <persName>Mr Isaac Minis</persName><lb/> has recd his Books &#38; Paid for it<lb/> should you have a nother <sic>sett</sic> of<lb/> the kind&#44; what comes any less<lb/> you can send one for <persName>Mr M Cohen</persName><lb/> he <sic>dont</sic> care how common the binding<lb/> is so that it cost less my friend<lb/> I am <sic>realy</sic> <sic>sory</sic> that I can not<lb/> do much for you in this Place<lb/> I can assure you that I have done<lb/> my best but they <sic>dont</sic> seem to<lb/> care much for such things<lb/> it is perfectly useless to keep those<lb/> Prayer Books &#38; Bibles <sic>hier</sic> the only<lb/> way is to send for when <sic>realy</sic> ordered<lb/> as I have done it would be my<lb/> order in that if you have any use<lb/> for those Prayer Books &#38; Bibles to let<lb/> them be send back all the money</p>
      <pb n="2"/>
        <p>is &#36;15&#8212; from <persName>Miss Ward</persName> &#38; &#36;12<lb/> from <persName>Mr I <add>&#63;</add></persName> <persName>Col Delamote</persName><lb/> <sic>intents</sic> to send some money to you<lb/> as I told him that I would like<lb/> to remit at the same time what<lb/> ever is in my hands coming to you<lb/> &#38; will be most happy to serve you<lb/> at all times believe me yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">most <sic>trully</sic> friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">R Mayers</persName></p>
		</body>
